org.lsmr.vending.frontend4.hardware

Interface AbstractProductAcceptor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DeliveryChute, ProductRack

    public interface AbstractProductAcceptor
    A simple interface to allow a device to communicate with another device that accepts products.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void acceptProduct(Product product)
      Instructs the device to take the product as input.

    • Method Detail

      • acceptProduct

        void acceptProduct(Product product)
            throws CapacityExceededException,
                   DisabledException
        Instructs the device to take the product as input.
        Parameters:
        product - The product to be taken as input. Cannot be null.
        Throws:
        CapacityExceededException - If the device does not have enough space for the product.
        DisabledException - If the device is currently disabled.

      • hasSpace

        boolean hasSpace()
        Checks whether the device has enough space to expect one more item. If this method returns true, an immediate call to acceptCoin should not throw CapacityExceededException, unless an asynchronous addition has occurred in the meantime.
        Returns:
        true if there is space, false if there is not space
